    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-11-14T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-11-14T16:00:00-05:00" n="34"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d34">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3231/572: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="13a" xml:id="d34fn13a">The Secretary of State was en route to the
                        Seventh International Conference of American States, held at Montevideo,
                        December 3–26, 1933; for correspondence concerning the Conference, see <ref
                            target="frus1933v04#pg_1">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>, pp. 1</ref>
                        ff.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>S. S. “<hi rend="smallcaps">American Legion</hi>,”</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-11-14T16:00:00">November 14, 1933—4
                            p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 4:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2. In order that I may be intelligently informed in case matter comes up in
                    conversations please radio any expansion of trade agreement plans with regard to
                    Brazilian and Argentine negotiations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
